-Flashes assets from the snapshot/ directory to eMMC.
+Flashes firmware assets from the snapshot/ directory to eMMC.
+
+## Flash firmware and kernel to eMMC
+
+```sh
+./flash.sh mmc-kernel
+```
+
+Flashes `idbloader.img`, `u-boot.itb`, and `kernel.img` from the snapshot/
+directory to eMMC. The root filesystem partition is not updated.
+Build `kernel.img` with `./linux.mk kernel` from `opencca-build/buildconf`.
+
+This command verifies that the target eMMC has the OpenCCA raw `kernel`
+partition at sector `0x8000` before writing. If the board was initialized with
+an older image whose root partition starts at sector `0x8000`, reflash the full
+rootfs image first so the kernel slot exists.
+
+## Flash rootfs to eMMC
+
+```sh
+./flash.sh mmc-rootfs
+```
+
+Flashes `opencca-rootfs-wip.ext4` from the snapshot/ directory to the rootfs
+partition at sector `0x48000`. Firmware and kernel partitions are not updated,
+and the board is not reset after the write.
+
+This command verifies that the target eMMC has a `root` partition at sector
+`0x48000` and that the selected image fits before writing.
+
+Use an explicit path to flash another ext4 image:
+
+```sh
+./flash.sh mmc-rootfs /path/to/rootfs.ext4
+```
+
+The default image path can also be set with `OPENCCA_ROOTFS_IMAGE`.
+
+## Convert older prebuilt image layout
+
+```sh
+python3 convert_prebuilt_image.py \
+  ../opencca-image-rockchip-rock5b-rk3588.img \
+  ../opencca-image-rockchip-rock5b-rk3588-compatible.img \
+  --kernel ../snapshot/kernel.img
+```
+
+This converts an older prebuilt image whose `root` partition starts at sector
+`0x8000` into the compatible layout used by `mmc-kernel` and `mmc-rootfs`.
+The output image contains a raw `kernel` partition at sector `0x8000` and moves
+the rootfs to sector `0x48000`. If the rootfs cannot shrink enough to fit after
+being shifted, the output image is expanded while preserving the rootfs.
 
